Section 1:
132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 983
S.P. 413 In Senate, March 11, 2025
Hospitalized Patients
Reference to the Committee on Judiciary suggested and ordered printed.
DAREK M. GRANT
Secretary of the Senate
Presented by Senator CARNEY of Cumberland.
Cosponsored by Representative KUHN of Falmouth and
Senators: BALDACCI of Penobscot, HAGGAN of Penobscot, Representative: LEE of Auburn.
Printed on recycled paper
1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 22 MRSA ยง1727, sub-ยง1-A is enacted to read:
3 1-A. Service of notice of restricted person status. A law enforcement agency may
4 request that a hospital provide access to a person who is receiving care in the hospital for
5 the purpose of notifying the person that the person is a restricted person as defined in Title
6 34-B, section 3862-A, subsection 1, paragraph K.
7 A. The hospital shall provide the law enforcement agency with an opportunity to notify
8 the person under this subsection at a time the hospital determines is clinically
9 appropriate with due consideration to the medical condition of the person.
10 B. A hospital may disclose that the person is a patient to facilitate notice under this
11 subsection regardless of patient consent.
12 SUMMARY
1133 This bill amends the law governing hospital cooperation with law enforcement
1144 agencies to allow a law enforcement agency to request that a hospital provide access to a
1155 patient for purposes of notification of restricted person status for a person taken into
1166 protective custody by a law enforcement officer due to likelihood of foreseeable harm.
